The paper proposes a new method for learning non-stationary spectral kernels using deep architectures and convolutional filters. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces regularizers and derives generalization error bounds, indicating that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method on real-world datasets, suggesting that it may also belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
